result.formatted_address: 98號 Soy St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: 魚魂 98

reviews.text:
We came for this signature beef hotpot with 180g of beef packed in a massive tower with tons of vegetables. It did take us quite some time to figure out how to eat it, as the pot was quite shallow and there wasn’t much soup as you can see.

We put aside the tower so that we can put the beef and vegetables in the pot bit by bit. I was actually quite surprise with the amount of beef. I thought there would only be one layer of beef, but it turned out to be a few layers! 180g of beef is quite a lot. Also, there were tons of vegetables! Seriously, we were glad that we didn’t order any carbs to go with the hotpot. We were all so stuff with the meat and greens. Kind of a balanced diet I guess? 

There are quite a few pork bone based soup base for you to choose from, and I chose the black truffle one. The black truffle made the vegetables so much more flavored and enjoyable to eat. That’s why a vegetables hate like me could finish the enormous amount of vegetables. Point to note, if you request for more soup, which you will need to at some point, it’s free, but it’s only pork bone based soup, not the one you order. So it kinda dilute the flavour of your soup…

It’s definitely money-worthy. But the service was not quite good, as in you don’t feel welcome at all, and what all the waitresses want is to get you out as soon as possible, when there isn’t even a queue outside the restaurants and still plenty of seats available…
Taste nice and really high quality services
Nice place.
Value for money set lunch
I got smoachache after having their hotpot

result.adr_address: 102 Soy St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 102 Soy St, Mong Kok, Hong Kong
result.name: The Concord Building

reviews.text: It's a hidden gem for residence in Hong Kong. Stunning view of the metropolis, unbeatable location, super convenient, many good restaurants downstairs and nearby. Perfect place for shopping and eating, but it's never noisy at night. Mongkok and Yau Ma Tei metro stations are just less than 10 mins walk, another 10 mins walk to Mongkok East train station which takes you directly to the New Territories or Lo Wu without hassel.
景觀一般
